Quote:  You'll hear a bit of barracking then; some young shearer has stolen a march on his faster mates and got onto the `money-side' first, and a bit of an ironic cheer goes up as he whips over the last hind leg and kicks his sheep out of the porthole a couple of seconds before anyone else.
